      "text": "Fields Breakdown for Sales Order",
      "fontSize": 28.989974881568944,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Fields Breakdown for Sales Order",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "N_vG3i9_VVhffjPA-5Zin",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 3825.6521164021174,
      "y": 614.1656127097317,
      "width": 1426.130859375,
      "height": 320,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 90,
      "groupIds": [
        "UAgVH8XIBVM9CpTLctrmT"
      ],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bMH",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1786296051,
      "version": 1633,
      "versionNonce": 492784657,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1780913622447,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "1. When a new Sales Order is created it should be created in Draft status. \n2. Customer : Name of Customer (store field) many2one (mandatory)\n3. Customer Address : Char Field max limit \n4. Creation Date: Auto populate date/time when a record is created.(here when a So is created using new button) make readonly once created.\n5. Sales Person: Dropdown field, with selection of users from database\n6. Products : Dropdown Selction field to select products from Product database. (track logs)\n7. Sales Price : Populate values from Product (track logs)\n8. Total : Ordered Qunatity* Sales Price (once delivered it should be delivered quantuity * Sales Price) (track logs)\n9. Availabilty: If Ordered Quantity is greater then Free to use quantity on product. (track logs)\n\nButtons:\nBack button: takes back to list view\nConfirm Button: changes Status from Draft to Confirm )(when confirm field like creation dtae, customer and customer address are readonly) (hide once status is change) (track logs)\nDeliver Button: 1. Change status to Fully Delivered if Delivered Quantity= Ordered Quantity (make all fields readonly and hide deliver button) (track logs)\n                    2. Change status to Partially Delivered if Delivered Quantity< Ordered Quantity (make all fields readonly , expect delivered quantity field. and show deliver button)\nCancel Button: Cancel Sale Order and make all fields readonly. (track logs)",
      "fontSize": 16,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "1. When a new Sales Order is created it should be created in Draft status. \n2. Customer : Name of Customer (store field) many2one (mandatory)\n3. Customer Address : Char Field max limit \n4. Creation Date: Auto populate date/time when a record is created.(here when a So is created using new button) make readonly once created.\n5. Sales Person: Dropdown field, with selection of users from database\n6. Products : Dropdown Selction field to select products from Product database. (track logs)\n7. Sales Price : Populate values from Product (track logs)\n8. Total : Ordered Qunatity* Sales Price (once delivered it should be delivered quantuity * Sales Price) (track logs)\n9. Availabilty: If Ordered Quantity is greater then Free to use quantity on product. (track logs)\n\nButtons:\nBack button: takes back to list view\nConfirm Button: changes Status from Draft to Confirm )(when confirm field like creation dtae, customer and customer address are readonly) (hide once status is change) (track logs)\nDeliver Button: 1. Change status to Fully Delivered if Delivered Quantity= Ordered Quantity (make all fields readonly and hide deliver button) (track logs)\n                    2. Change status to Partially Delivered if Delivered Quantity< Ordered Quantity (make all fields readonly , expect delivered quantity field. and show deliver button)\nCancel Button: Cancel Sale Order and make all fields readonly. (track logs)",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
