    {
      "id": "1DTi4Orwxen44SSs1NU8J",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 3911.154405779405,
      "y": 1915.7912677390102,
      "width": 1692.1798095703125,
      "height": 500,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 90,
      "groupIds": [
        "9JtoRJQyldgqy7hsm7HR9"
      ],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bMO",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 214154589,
      "version": 3804,
      "versionNonce": 495107792,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1780309871219,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "1. When a new Manufacturing  Order is created it should be created in Draft status.\n2. Finished Product : Dropdown selection field, allow to selct products form product Database (store field) many2one (mandatory) (track logs)\n3. Quantity : Quantity to be Produced of Finished Good  (track logs)\n5. Assignee: Dropdown field, with selection of users from database \n6. Bill of Materials : Dropdown Selction field to select Bill of Materials from Bill of Materials database.(if Finished Product is enter first , only bill of materials for that product only)   (track logs)  \n\nSections: Components : \nComponents: Populate values from Bill of Materials if added , if not added allow to products from product database. (track logs)\nTo Consume quantity: Populate based on Bill of Materials values (numeric field) (track logs)\nConsumed Quantity : Allow to enter value mannually (numeric field). Show once Manufacturing is in Confirmed state. Make it readonly when MO is in Done/Cancelled Status.(track logs)\nAvaliability: Show Avaialble , if there is Free to use quantity = to consume quantity from product., No not show Not Available. \n\nSections Work Orders:\nOperation: Popluate from Bill of Materials , If none allow user to add a line, when MO is in Draft, Confirmed or In-progress status.\nWork Center: Populate from Bill of Materials, (Mandatory field while adding an operation)  readonly when MO is in Done/Cancelled status.\nExpected Duration: Populate based on Bill Materials, if none, then its should be time field in minutes, Expected duration should change based on change in MO quantity , (track logs)\n                            For example, if expected duration in Bill of materials for qty=1 is 10 mins, and MO is of 10 qty, the expected duration in MO should be 100 mins.(read-only when MO is in Done/Cancelled Status).\nReal Duration: Time Field, and allow user to enter when Mo is in Confirmed /Inprogress status. For Draft status =Hide, Readonly when Status= Done/Cancelled. (track logs)\n             \n        \nButtons:\nBack button: takes back to list view\nConfirm Button: changes Status from Draft to Confirm )(when confirm field like creation date, Finished Product and Bill of Materials  are readonly) (hide once status is change) (track logs)\nProduce Button: When Clicked, Mark MO as Done status, MAke all field on MO readonly. (track logs)\nCancel Button: Cancel Manufacturing Order and make all fields readonly. (track logs) ",
      "fontSize": 16,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "1. When a new Manufacturing  Order is created it should be created in Draft status.\n2. Finished Product : Dropdown selection field, allow to selct products form product Database (store field) many2one (mandatory) (track logs)\n3. Quantity : Quantity to be Produced of Finished Good  (track logs)\n5. Assignee: Dropdown field, with selection of users from database \n6. Bill of Materials : Dropdown Selction field to select Bill of Materials from Bill of Materials database.(if Finished Product is enter first , only bill of materials for that product only)   (track logs)  \n\nSections: Components : \nComponents: Populate values from Bill of Materials if added , if not added allow to products from product database. (track logs)\nTo Consume quantity: Populate based on Bill of Materials values (numeric field) (track logs)\nConsumed Quantity : Allow to enter value mannually (numeric field). Show once Manufacturing is in Confirmed state. Make it readonly when MO is in Done/Cancelled Status.(track logs)\nAvaliability: Show Avaialble , if there is Free to use quantity = to consume quantity from product., No not show Not Available. \n\nSections Work Orders:\nOperation: Popluate from Bill of Materials , If none allow user to add a line, when MO is in Draft, Confirmed or In-progress status.\nWork Center: Populate from Bill of Materials, (Mandatory field while adding an operation)  readonly when MO is in Done/Cancelled status.\nExpected Duration: Populate based on Bill Materials, if none, then its should be time field in minutes, Expected duration should change based on change in MO quantity , (track logs)\n                            For example, if expected duration in Bill of materials for qty=1 is 10 mins, and MO is of 10 qty, the expected duration in MO should be 100 mins.(read-only when MO is in Done/Cancelled Status).\nReal Duration: Time Field, and allow user to enter when Mo is in Confirmed /Inprogress status. For Draft status =Hide, Readonly when Status= Done/Cancelled. (track logs)\n             \n        \nButtons:\nBack button: takes back to list view\nConfirm Button: changes Status from Draft to Confirm )(when confirm field like creation date, Finished Product and Bill of Materials  are readonly) (hide once status is change) (track logs)\nProduce Button: When Clicked, Mark MO as Done status, MAke all field on MO readonly. (track logs)\nCancel Button: Cancel Manufacturing Order and make all fields readonly. (track logs) ",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
