    },
    {
      "id": "6FBLPFkTuNpjnh-yu5tVm",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 3067.02116402116,
      "y": 3455.864025408144,
      "width": 1688.979736328125,
      "height": 480,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 90,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bMW",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1849871285,
      "version": 2934,
      "versionNonce": 710492394,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1779789065357,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "1. Product : Char field, create Product based on it.  (track logs)\n2. Sales Price: Monetary Field, should be poopulated on sales order, if this product is added on Sales Order. (track logs)\n\n3. Cost Price : Monetary Field, Should be populated on Purchase Order, if this product is added on Purchase Order (track logs)\n\n4. On Hand Qty: Numeric field with decimal values allowed.  (track logs)\n                    a)Should increase by quantity on purchase order, when a product is recieved.(based on recieved quantity) ( PO= status Done)\n                    b) Should increase by quantity on Manufacturing , if added as finished good and its manufactured. (based on produced quantity) (MO = Status done)\n                    c) Should decrease by Consumed quantity on Manufacturing Order of Components, if the product is added as component. (MO= status Done)\n                    d) Should decrease by delievered quantity on sales order, when this product is delivered on sales order.(SO= satuts fully delievered)\n\n5. Free to Use Qty : On Hand qty- Reserved Quantity  Reserved Quantity is only considered when Orders are in Confirmed or Inprogress state (Readonly field for everyone, only compute value)\n                    Calculation for reserved quantity: a) If the product is added on Sales Order and Status of Sales Order is not yet fully delievered , the reserved quantity is Delievered quantity.\n                                                              b) If the product is added on Manufacturing Order Component and MO is not yet in Done status, the Consume quantity = Reserved Quantity.\n\n6. Procure on Demand: Add a Checkbox when checked, added a  mandatory field with dropdown (Purchase and Manufacturing). (track logs)\n                            When checked add a field based on selcteion, If Purchase is selected added field \"Vendor\", If Manufacturing is Selecxted add a Field \"BoM\"   (mandatory fields)(track logs)\n                            Vendor: Selection from Vendor Name records , Bill of Materials : Selction form Bill of Materials records. (track logs)\n\nWhen Procure on Demand is Checked : If On Hand Qty is less then Sales Order Qty, Trigger a Procurement(i.e Create a new A pruchase order is Purchase is selected and for the vendor as specified for the remaining \ndifference quantity,  or create a new Manufacturing Order if Manufacturing is selected and for the bill of materials specified for the difference quantity).\n\nWhen unchecked, no purchase or manufacturing order should be created.\n                                                ",
      "fontSize": 16,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "1. Product : Char field, create Product based on it.  (track logs)\n2. Sales Price: Monetary Field, should be poopulated on sales order, if this product is added on Sales Order. (track logs)\n\n3. Cost Price : Monetary Field, Should be populated on Purchase Order, if this product is added on Purchase Order (track logs)\n\n4. On Hand Qty: Numeric field with decimal values allowed.  (track logs)\n                    a)Should increase by quantity on purchase order, when a product is recieved.(based on recieved quantity) ( PO= status Done)\n                    b) Should increase by quantity on Manufacturing , if added as finished good and its manufactured. (based on produced quantity) (MO = Status done)\n                    c) Should decrease by Consumed quantity on Manufacturing Order of Components, if the product is added as component. (MO= status Done)\n                    d) Should decrease by delievered quantity on sales order, when this product is delivered on sales order.(SO= satuts fully delievered)\n\n5. Free to Use Qty : On Hand qty- Reserved Quantity  Reserved Quantity is only considered when Orders are in Confirmed or Inprogress state (Readonly field for everyone, only compute value)\n                    Calculation for reserved quantity: a) If the product is added on Sales Order and Status of Sales Order is not yet fully delievered , the reserved quantity is Delievered quantity.\n                                                              b) If the product is added on Manufacturing Order Component and MO is not yet in Done status, the Consume quantity = Reserved Quantity.\n\n6. Procure on Demand: Add a Checkbox when checked, added a  mandatory field with dropdown (Purchase and Manufacturing). (track logs)\n                            When checked add a field based on selcteion, If Purchase is selected added field \"Vendor\", If Manufacturing is Selecxted add a Field \"BoM\"   (mandatory fields)(track logs)\n                            Vendor: Selection from Vendor Name records , Bill of Materials : Selction form Bill of Materials records. (track logs)\n\nWhen Procure on Demand is Checked : If On Hand Qty is less then Sales Order Qty, Trigger a Procurement(i.e Create a new A pruchase order is Purchase is selected and for the vendor as specified for the remaining \ndifference quantity,  or create a new Manufacturing Order if Manufacturing is selected and for the bill of materials specified for the difference quantity).\n\nWhen unchecked, no purchase or manufacturing order should be created.\n                                                ",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
